1
00:01:36,479 --> 00:01:39,990
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:42,039
[Episode 21]

3
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:00,630
Hello, Mom.

4
00:02:00,630 --> 00:02:01,430
Xingchi!

5
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:04,350
What have you been doing? Your phone has been off all day.

6
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:07,310
My phone ran out of battery.

7
00:02:07,810 --> 00:02:09,259
I just charged it. What's wrong?

8
00:02:09,789 --> 00:02:11,450
We were worried about you.

9
00:02:12,950 --> 00:02:14,320
I'm a grown-up now.

10
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:15,710
You don't have to worry about me.

11
00:02:16,079 --> 00:02:17,040
I'm fine.

12
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:18,200
Don't worry, Mom.

13
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:19,230
What do you mean "don't worry"?

14
00:02:19,270 --> 00:02:19,829
Listen to me.

15
00:02:19,829 --> 00:02:21,950
From now on, don't ever...

16
00:02:22,670 --> 00:02:24,040
...Just keep your phone on.

17
00:02:24,260 --> 00:02:26,740
I called you because I wanted to tell you that

18
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:27,829
your dad

19
00:02:27,860 --> 00:02:29,500
has arranged with Mr. Du

20
00:02:29,710 --> 00:02:31,490
for you to learn bamboo carving from him.

21
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:32,670
Bamboo carving?

22
00:02:32,690 --> 00:02:34,900
That's an intangible cultural heritage.

23
00:02:35,310 --> 00:02:35,950
Xingchi.

24
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:36,910
Listen.

25
00:02:37,070 --> 00:02:38,190
Your Uncle Du

26
00:02:38,270 --> 00:02:40,030
is a famous bamboo carving master.

27
00:02:40,070 --> 00:02:41,310
He's doing me a great favor,

28
00:02:41,310 --> 00:02:43,030
being willing to take you as an apprentice.

29
00:02:43,070 --> 00:02:43,350
Right.

30
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:45,690
[Hang up]

31
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:45,690
[Mom]

32
00:02:43,350 --> 00:02:44,690
I'm telling you, stop messing around out there.

33
00:02:44,730 --> 00:02:45,870
Just come back home.

34
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:48,820
What happened?

35
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,610
He hung up, that's what happened.

36
00:02:50,710 --> 00:02:53,110
Try... Try calling him again. It must have been a disconnection.

37
00:02:59,720 --> 00:02:59,970
[Hang up]

38
00:02:59,720 --> 00:02:59,970
[Mom]

39
00:03:00,070 --> 00:03:02,770
[Turn off] [Reboot]

40
00:03:04,070 --> 00:03:06,110
The subscriber you dialed is power off.

41
00:03:07,230 --> 00:03:08,070
He turned off his phone.

42
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,870
Look at him.

43
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:11,150
How can he be so immature?

44
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:13,150
Look at Wanghe,

45
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:14,540
Haikuo, and Fenghua,

46
00:03:14,730 --> 00:03:15,150
right?

47
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:16,150
They're becoming more and more filial.

48
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:17,470
And here he is, almost 30,

49
00:03:17,490 --> 00:03:18,530
yet still in his rebellious phase.

50
00:03:18,550 --> 00:03:19,950
Just criticize Xingchi if you want to.

51
00:03:19,990 --> 00:03:20,990
Why do you have to get the other kids involved?

52
00:03:20,990 --> 00:03:21,829
Who should I compare him to

53
00:03:21,870 --> 00:03:22,680
if not them?

54
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:24,000
You know the saying, to feed without teaching

55
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,079
is the father's fault.

56
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,000
So it's all my fault, you mean?

57
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:29,470
I shouldn't have let him go to Beijing!

58
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:46,090
[West Zhongguancun]

59
00:03:46,270 --> 00:03:47,890
This is an express delivery station, you know?

60
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:51,290
[Fenghua Express]

61
00:03:47,940 --> 00:03:49,370
It's not a soup kitchen.

62
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,520
Why should we provide for your whole family?

63
00:03:50,670 --> 00:03:51,470
Look at your family,

64
00:03:51,510 --> 00:03:52,680
eating and drinking so much.

65
00:03:52,890 --> 00:03:53,960
Who can afford to support you?

66
00:03:55,030 --> 00:03:56,150
I don't want to leave.

67
00:03:57,230 --> 00:04:00,230
I don't want to... I don't want to go.

68
00:04:02,950 --> 00:04:04,490
Fenghua is here.

69
00:04:04,630 --> 00:04:05,630
Sun, what's going on?

70
00:04:05,670 --> 00:04:07,460
Fenghua! You're finally back.

71
00:04:07,510 --> 00:04:07,750
It's alright.

72
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:08,910
How many times have I told you?

73
00:04:08,910 --> 00:04:09,750
Our station

74
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,190
is just this small courtyard

75
00:04:11,230 --> 00:04:12,230
that can only hold over a dozen people.

76
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:13,740
We can't afford to support freeloaders.

77
00:04:14,370 --> 00:04:16,089
If He Tianming wants to work here, that's okay.

78
00:04:16,110 --> 00:04:17,820
But bringing his whole family here

79
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:18,649
is not acceptable.

80
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,260
He Tianming.

81
00:04:23,370 --> 00:04:24,460
If you want to work here,

82
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,680
then work properly.

83
00:04:26,290 --> 00:04:27,510
Find another place to accommodate

84
00:04:27,510 --> 00:04:29,160
your wife, child, and mother.

85
00:04:29,450 --> 00:04:30,680
You can't cause trouble

86
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,200
for the station, you know?

87
00:04:33,140 --> 00:04:35,830
So where do you want our whole family

88
00:04:35,909 --> 00:04:37,550
to live?

89
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:39,200
Beijing is such a big city.

90
00:04:39,350 --> 00:04:40,070
If you spend a little money,

91
00:04:40,070 --> 00:04:41,480
you can find a place to live, can't you?

92
00:04:41,770 --> 00:04:42,930
If you really can't manage,

93
00:04:43,530 --> 00:04:44,960
go live under a bridge.

94
00:04:48,470 --> 00:04:49,520
Enough!

95
00:04:49,909 --> 00:04:50,750
Why are you all standing here?

96
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,450
Packages have arrived. Hurry up and send them out.

97
00:04:52,740 --> 00:04:53,870
Didn't you hear what Mr. Sun said?

98
00:04:53,909 --> 00:04:55,150
We don't keep idle people here.

99
00:04:55,390 --> 00:04:57,640
He, take them and get those packages sent out quickly.

100
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,390
Auntie, go cook.

101
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:01,120
Okay.

102
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,340
Let's go.

103
00:05:02,380 --> 00:05:03,200
Let's go.

104
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:04,970
I'll take the child to cook.

105
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:05,670
Okay.

106
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:07,670
It's almost mealtime. Hurry up and go.

107
00:05:09,460 --> 00:05:10,350
Hey, Xia Fenghua.

108
00:05:10,380 --> 00:05:11,340
What's that supposed to mean?

109
00:05:12,910 --> 00:05:13,920
Don't talk out here.

110
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,220
Let's go talk in the office.

111
00:05:18,850 --> 00:05:19,690
Come on, let's talk there.

112
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:35,010
Have a glass of water first and calm down.

113
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:39,100
You know we're running a business here, right?

114
00:05:39,590 --> 00:05:41,030
This isn't a charity.

115
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:42,710
Have you ever seen anyone

116
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,909
bring the whole family along when doing business?

117
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,060
Their family's situation is special.

118
00:05:47,230 --> 00:05:49,390
Besides, He is capable.

119
00:05:49,409 --> 00:05:50,150
He might be capable,

120
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,630
but can he handle the workload of three people?

121
00:05:51,670 --> 00:05:53,470
Do you know there are four people in his family?

122
00:05:54,050 --> 00:05:55,150
How can you support all of them?

123
00:05:55,670 --> 00:05:57,190
But they're not just sitting around.

124
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,670
His mother cooks for the station,

125
00:05:58,750 --> 00:05:59,990
and his wife helps with sorting.

126
00:05:59,990 --> 00:06:01,440
They're all quite busy usually.

127
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:04,620
Are they your relatives?

128
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:07,360
No, they're not.

129
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:10,080
He and I were colleagues before.

130
00:06:10,110 --> 00:06:11,390
We handed out flyers

131
00:06:11,430 --> 00:06:12,570
and sold phone cases together.

132
00:06:13,310 --> 00:06:14,900
I know his family is indigent.

133
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:16,470
I was just thinking,

134
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:17,710
since they can offer manpower

135
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:18,590
and they're not lazy,

136
00:06:18,670 --> 00:06:19,870
why can't we all work together?

137
00:06:20,430 --> 00:06:22,270
Besides, they're really not staying here for free.

138
00:06:22,310 --> 00:06:23,310
Not for free?

139
00:06:23,940 --> 00:06:26,300
You call that little money "not staying for free"?

140
00:06:27,210 --> 00:06:28,210
Remember when

141
00:06:28,550 --> 00:06:30,220
we set up this station together?

142
00:06:30,260 --> 00:06:31,190
How difficult it was!

143
00:06:31,220 --> 00:06:33,130
Why did you have to bring in some old, weak, sick, and disabled people?

144
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:42,670
Sun, how about this?

145
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,940
Do me a favor and

146
00:06:44,950 --> 00:06:46,130
let them stay for a few more days.

147
00:06:46,850 --> 00:06:47,900
He said

148
00:06:47,909 --> 00:06:49,230
he's looking for a place.

149
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:50,590
As soon as he finds one, they'll move out immediately.

150
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:51,750
It has to be today.

151
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,340
They must leave immediately!

152
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:54,760
Sun.

153
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:56,159
Xia Fenghua.

154
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:58,150
Have you lost your mind?

155
00:06:58,260 --> 00:06:59,950
Have you even lifted yourself out of poverty?

156
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:02,230
Yet you're thinking of helping others?

157
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,670
Are you in any position to do that?

158
00:07:04,990 --> 00:07:05,720
Sun Daqing.

159
00:07:07,930 --> 00:07:09,420
Since you've brought this up,

160
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:11,270
let's get things straight.

161
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:14,640
This station was originally contracted by me alone.

162
00:07:14,660 --> 00:07:16,980
I only brought you in because you wanted to join.

163
00:07:17,670 --> 00:07:18,870
Today, without my consent,

164
00:07:18,870 --> 00:07:20,400
you tried to drive my employee away.

165
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,760
You have no right to do that.

166
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:22,860
For one station,

167
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,140
there's only so much money it can make.

168
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:25,880
If you give more to others,

169
00:07:25,990 --> 00:07:27,630
there's less left for us to share.

170
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:29,420
Can't you do this simple math?

171
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:32,240
Did you buy that self-study diploma?

172
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:41,750
Cut the crap.

173
00:07:42,370 --> 00:07:43,810
Settle the accounts right away

174
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:45,070
and leave!

175
00:07:45,550 --> 00:07:47,290
From now on,

176
00:07:47,420 --> 00:07:48,360
I'll run this station myself!

177
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:49,950
Way to go, Xia Fenghua.

178
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:51,490
Don't you regret it.

179
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:53,290
From now on,

180
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:54,870
let's go

181
00:07:54,370 --> 00:07:57,930
[Sorting Area (Urban Area)]

182
00:07:54,870 --> 00:07:55,950
our separate ways!

183
00:07:59,940 --> 00:08:00,790
Come in.

184
00:08:08,790 --> 00:08:10,790
Fenghua, I'm sorry.

185
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:12,820
This is my own decision.

186
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:14,020
It has nothing to do with you.

187
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:16,670
Sun and I don't get along.

188
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:18,540
Splitting up was bound to happen sooner or later.

189
00:08:21,130 --> 00:08:21,940
From now on,

190
00:08:21,970 --> 00:08:23,020
we'll run this station ourselves.

191
00:08:23,150 --> 00:08:25,510
The earth keeps spinning, regardless of who's here or not.

192
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:27,740
What about

193
00:08:28,090 --> 00:08:29,590
the business Mr. Sun brought in?

194
00:08:29,810 --> 00:08:31,250
He took all the business with him.

195
00:08:31,790 --> 00:08:33,059
We'll find new business later.

196
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:42,130
No matter how much business we lose,

197
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:43,600
we'll make it up in the future.

198
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:45,130
But

199
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:48,430
you have to help me with some of the management work.

200
00:08:48,630 --> 00:08:49,830
We can't afford it now,

201
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,840
so I won't be able to pay you extra.

202
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,110
No need, Fenghua.

203
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:54,460
We're already extremely grateful

204
00:08:54,710 --> 00:08:56,130
to you for keeping us on.

205
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:57,840
Don't worry, Fenghua.

206
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:59,650
My whole family will work hard from now on.

207
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:01,030
We won't let you regret it.

208
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:04,030
Alright, get back to work.

209
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,020
This exhibition of ours

210
00:09:12,020 --> 00:09:14,070
provides a detailed introduction to the history of the canal's evolution

211
00:09:14,070 --> 00:09:16,470
through numerous artifacts and images.

212
00:09:15,970 --> 00:09:22,060
[Honghuai Grand Canal Expo]

213
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:18,710
Please take a closer look.

214
00:09:22,390 --> 00:09:24,390
Well, speaking of the Grand Canal,

215
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:25,840
we all know that

216
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:29,260
it's the greatest hydraulic engineering project of ancient times,

217
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,750
bar none.

218
00:09:31,930 --> 00:09:35,080
In fact, starting from the Spring and Autumn and Warring States periods,

219
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:36,240
up until today,

220
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,900
our country has continuously

221
00:09:37,950 --> 00:09:40,550
been constructing and dredging the Grand Canal.

222
00:09:40,590 --> 00:09:42,030
After the founding of New China,

223
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:44,270
in 1953 and 1957,

224
00:09:44,270 --> 00:09:47,110
the Jiangyin Lock and Yangliuqing Lock were built,

225
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:49,420
as well as thousand-ton locks like the Suqian Lock.

226
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:50,270
After 1959,

227
00:09:50,270 --> 00:09:52,200
to support the South-to-North Water Diversion Project,

228
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:54,630
the section from Xuzhou to the Yangtze River was expanded as a key project,

229
00:09:52,930 --> 00:09:58,120
[Lively Jiangnan]

230
00:09:54,630 --> 00:09:56,830
which is about 400 kilometers of the canal.

231
00:09:57,570 --> 00:10:00,090
This increased the canal's annual one-way capacity

232
00:10:00,270 --> 00:10:02,250
to nearly 20 million tons.

233
00:10:02,990 --> 00:10:04,150
It also expanded

234
00:10:04,190 --> 00:10:06,630
the irrigated and drained areas along the canal.

235
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:08,900
This measure

236
00:10:08,940 --> 00:10:10,350
ensured the safety of people's lives and property

237
00:10:10,350 --> 00:10:11,870
along the canal,

238
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:14,050
as well as the development of agricultural production.

239
00:10:14,230 --> 00:10:16,250
Therefore, this project has achieved

240
00:10:16,460 --> 00:10:18,180
social benefits in various aspects.

241
00:10:19,770 --> 00:10:21,150
However, there's one point

242
00:10:21,190 --> 00:10:22,590
I want to emphasize today.

243
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:24,190
That is, through this exhibition,

244
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:25,350
you may have felt that

245
00:10:25,380 --> 00:10:26,550
this rich heritage

246
00:10:26,550 --> 00:10:28,890
left by our ancestors

247
00:10:28,950 --> 00:10:30,030
is still benefiting us descendants

248
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:31,750
[Footage of the Sunken Ship]

249
00:10:30,070 --> 00:10:32,300
until this day.

250
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:38,910
[Canal of Plenty]

251
00:10:32,990 --> 00:10:33,910
Therefore,

252
00:10:34,310 --> 00:10:36,230
we should sincerely exclaim that

253
00:10:36,230 --> 00:10:38,750
this is indeed a great project.

254
00:10:41,170 --> 00:10:41,830
Bravo.

255
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,010
Mr. Zhou.

256
00:10:48,110 --> 00:10:49,170
Come and take a look at this.

257
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,190
Come on, check this out.

258
00:10:54,990 --> 00:10:55,760
What is this?

259
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:56,980
An arrow.

260
00:10:57,230 --> 00:10:58,550
Mr. Chen found this

261
00:10:58,590 --> 00:11:00,070
on the ship. On the side of the ship.

262
00:11:00,990 --> 00:11:02,180
I found it just now.

263
00:11:02,630 --> 00:11:03,550
You know what it proves?

264
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:04,460
That this ship

265
00:11:04,910 --> 00:11:05,790
was attacked.

266
00:11:06,550 --> 00:11:07,770
Attacked by whom?

267
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:10,850
How would I know?

268
00:11:11,230 --> 00:11:12,220
We'll have to wait for

269
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:14,200
further identification by archaeological experts.

270
00:11:18,710 --> 00:11:19,860
If you ask me,

271
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:21,580
this ship from late Qing dynasty,

272
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:22,720
which is less than 100 years old,

273
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,050
really doesn't have much archaeological value.

274
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:26,370
It's been seven years since we started investigating,

275
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:27,770
and nothing was found.

276
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:29,910
We don't even know

277
00:11:29,950 --> 00:11:31,230
who the owner of this ship was.

278
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:32,070
We do know.

279
00:11:32,830 --> 00:11:34,390
The owner was an Italian.

280
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:37,470
We don't even know his name.

281
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,380
It's not even recorded in the county chronicles.

282
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:41,530
